About Me

Hi, My name Ashling Smith and I am a 3rd year Creative Digital Media student in ITB, from Dublin. I am passionate about all things Design. My interests are web developement, design and branding. I have worked with clients on web development projects and volunteered with companies to help them have an online presence. My favorite part of designing is the research, and the beginning of a new project to the final result, It is always a satisfying feeling to see the final design. Over this summer I worked with Vodafone Germany, my job was to locate 5 technology companies around Dublin to participate in the project and to find show us via live streaming there innovative projects ...

App Concept Design

App Concept Design | I realised there was an opportunity to make it easier for client and designers relationship, through personal experience with clients, I felt designing and creating an app that the client can log into and see the progress on there project that the designer is undertaking for them. It will also contain deadline milestones and a contact section for the client to ask the designer questions. It can also be customised by the designer to suit his or hers business *note this is only a concept design*

Magazine Design

See Magazine

Magazine Design | I created a magazine using Adobe InDesign, I wanted to create a design magazine and feature some of my work that I created. My main design was a poly art design I did and I also created a tutorial section for anyone that wants to learn how to make there own poly art. It was a good experience making a magazine design and I am currently working on more.

About Ashling

Hi, My name Ashling Smith and I am a 3rd year Creative Digital Media student in ITB, from Dublin. I am passionate about all things Design. My interests are web developement, design and branding. I have worked with clients on web development projects and volunteered with companies to help them have an online presence. My favorite part of designing is the research, and the beginning of a new project to the final result, It is always a satisfying feeling to see the final design. Over this summer I worked with Vodafone Germany, my job was to locate 5 technology companies around Dublin to participate in the project and to find show us via live streaming there innovative projects. I participated in the live streaming as the hosts local guide and showed them around Dublin, also introducing them to the companies. It was a great experience to be apart of the Vodafone Germany #izddw project. Currently I am seeking an internship to apply my experience assisting a companys service to their clients using my skills in Digital Media. Specialties Brand Identity Design Web Design and Development (HTML, CSS, Java, Wordpress) Adobe Suite (Photoshop, Illustrator, InDesign, Premier Pro, After Effects) I have recently started a shop on Society6 doing Digital Art. Photoshop and illustrator are the tools I use to create my digital art.

#izddw Dublin Highlights

The Vodafone Germany Live streaming was live for 5 hours on the 19th July 2016, the video show the highlights of the Live streaming The Companies Involved were: Science Gallery XModule Love&Robots Epic Ireland  

My Skills are Focused on

Graphic Design
I design using programes such as Adobe Photoshop, Illustrator and InDesign
Web Design
Skilled at designing and developing websites using HTML, CSS, Java and building with CMS
Branding
I develop and design brands for clients and improve on their presence online

Interested in my CV?

If you are interested in knowing more about my work experience you can look at my CV or you can contact me by email | hello@ashlingsmith.ie

Take a Peek!

  • Your Inner Hero

  • Charleigh Bailey Website

  • FingalCEH Website

Say Hello!

Simple Hellos or Inquires | hello@ashlingsmith.ie

About Ashling

Hi, My name Ashling Smith and I am a 3rd year Creative Digital Media student in ITB, from Dublin. I am passionate about all things Design. My interests are web developement, design and branding. I have worked with clients on web development projects and volunteered with companies to help them have an online presence. My favorite part of designing is the research, and the beginning of a new project to the final result, It is always a satisfying feeling to see the final design. Over this summer I worked with Vodafone Germany, my job was to locate 5 technology companies around Dublin to participate in the project and to find show us via live streaming there innovative projects. I participated in the live streaming as the hosts local guide and showed them around Dublin, also introducing them to the companies. It was a great experience to be apart of the Vodafone Germany #izddw project.

Currently I am seeking an internship to apply my experience assisting a companys service to their clients using my skills in Digital Media.

Specialties
Brand Identity
Design
Web Design and Development (HTML, CSS, Java, Wordpress)
Adobe Suite (Photoshop, Illustrator, InDesign, Premier Pro, After Effects)

I have recently started a shop on Society6 doing Digital Art. Photoshop and illustrator are the tools I use to create my digital art.

item.title: Sample Page
item.dc:creator: ad_ashsm_29
item.content:encoded:
This is an example page. It's different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:
Hi there! I'm a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my blog. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like piña coladas. (And gettin' caught in the rain.)
...or something like this:
The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.
As a new WordPress user, you should go to your dashboard to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!

item.title: Great Place to Find Free Stock Images
item.dc:creator: ad_ashsm_29
item.content:encoded: Who doesn't love the word Free and especially when its got to do with designing. I always found it quite difficult to find completely free stock images without there always being a catch, making us go through a painful process to get an image and then you have to sign up or pay, but with some research I found a site that is free for commercial use and one that I use myself. Pixabay My favourite site for free images all open source and for commercial use, its images that artists or photographers put up to allow anyone to use them, you can also put your own images as well no catch at all. Ooh and did I mention there all free !! via GIPHY

item.title: Where to Start with WordPress
item.dc:creator: ad_ashsm_29
item.content:encoded: I have looked at many tutorials on how to start building a WordPress site but my Favorited website to find tutorials and guidance is wpbeginner. This website has everything you need to know on plugins, how to create blogs and customise themes. You can also follow them on twitter and see the updates they post on WordPress. I would also recommend following WordPress themselves on twitter to see recent updates and things you should know.

item.dc:creator: ad_ashsm_29
item.content:encoded:
Orderpoint Branding

Orderpoint | Order Point is a wearable point of sales system worn at the wrist, it is a direct two way communication system between the waiters and the kitchen staff who will accept the order through a tablet build system. The brand needs to show modern and futuristic elements, it needs to convey a sense of security to its buyers also aligning with stability and effective use. Order Point needs to stand out from its competition and show that its not just another point of sales system but more.

The Orderpoint logo uses three colors: Blue, black, and white. Primarily the logo should be used on a black background for maximum impact and clarity.

Orderpoint Watch Mockup | Shown is a mock-up version of what the logo will look like when displayed on the watch design. Its has a clear view point on the watch display.
